    An export context for model properties displayed as a column in a GenericTableDialog.

    Creating GenericTableContexts From An Exporter

    The following code snippet creates a GenericTableContext for a PerturbControlRod's bias_rod_comp property, where each PerturbControlRod is represented as a subblock array with the property name pert_crod. 
     var rodCompContext = new GenericTableContext(getPert_crod(i),
                                              "pert_crod",
                                              "bias_rod_comp");
    Associating GenericTableModel columns with GenericTableContext objects

    When building a GenericTMColumn, that column can be associated with a context object by utilizing the PropertyContextType class. The GenericTableContext class features the static utility method typeForColumn which will generate the appropriate PropertyContextType for a subblock property that is represented as a GenericTMColumn.
    The following code snippet shows how to create a PropertyContextType that matches with the context created in the example above. 
     var type = GenericTableContext.forColumn(PerturbControlRod.class, "bias_rod_comp");
    When a GenericTableDialog receives a GenericTableContext, the dialog can ask the context for its context type, which utilizes the same forColumn method shown above. The dialog can then search through a set of GenericTMColumns and find the column that has the matching context type.
